# Accountability guide updates — 2026-05-18

Source: `Perseus Jira (3).csv` (provided 2026-05-18).
Scope: SC / Accountability curated guides only. Assumption: existing guides reflect product state as of 2022-12-31; the CSV's resolved tickets are the authoritative source for changes since 2023-01-01.

Files modified: 7 curated `.md` files (9 logical changes / 10 inline citation comments).
Files NOT modified: any `.raw.md`, `.md.legacy`, `manifest.csv`, `failures.csv`, `raw/guides/snapshots/`, `raw/guides/diffs/`, or any non-Accountability path.

> **Revision note (2026-05-18, second pass after SME pushback):**
> - NXT-58287 reasoning rewritten — peer ticket to NXT-58225, not a discarded conflict (same resolved timestamp; the "more recently resolved wins" rule does not apply).
> - NXT-65306 applied to GUIDE-021 (it has a clear navigation surface: new setting, new exception type, new resolution method). My first pass had silently dropped it under a misapplied "behavior is Jira's authority" reading.
> - NXT-67405 kept out of guide content, but is now explicitly flagged below with reasoning instead of being lumped under a one-line "skipped" note.
> - GUIDE-025 candidates are now enumerated individually (48 rows) with per-ticket disposition, instead of a single-sentence summary.

