| NXT-65306 | 2025-10-29 | New "Attendance-driven Edit Checks (Daily Attendance, SNP only)" subsection appended after Resolve Edit Checks | (absent) | New subsection naming the gating system setting ("Edit checks for daily attendance counts?"), the new exception type and its reason text ("Attendance count exceeds enrolled count"), the two resolution paths (inline attendance-grid pop-up or comment + link to the Attendance page), and the recomputation of the existing "exceeds attendance factor" exception from daily counts. | When the Attendance Feature is active with the Daily Method and the new system setting is enabled, the Edit Checks page surfaces new exception types and a new resolution UI tied to the per-site/per-date attendance count. SNP only. The user's clickpath changes (new setting visible, new exception reason text on the page, new resolution flow), so this is navigation-relevant despite being a behavior-driven feature. |

Peer tickets (same resolved date, not a conflict):
- NXT-58287 (resolved 2025-02-19, "Reverse Edit Checks - Calculations"): same release as NXT-58225, covering the rolling-average computation, % under-average thresholds, and which meal types are surfaced. No standalone navigation surface to document — the user-visible UI changes are fully covered by NXT-58225. *Not a discarded conflict*; the conflict rule (more recently resolved wins) doesn't apply because both resolved at the same timestamp.

Flagged for human review (CLAUDE.md authority: behavior belongs in Jira, not the navigation guide):
- NXT-67405 (resolved 2025-11-14, "Updates for CACFP and CEP"): tightens edit-check flagging logic — only flag when count > threshold (not ≥); CEP/P2 sites flag only Total counts (not F/R/P); CACFP sites flag for all eligibilities, meal types, attendance, and totals. The user's clickpath through GUIDE-021 (view → resolve → comment) is unchanged; the only visible effect is *which rows appear* in the table, which is behavior. Per CLAUDE.md's authority rule ("Jira tickets/specs remain authoritative for behavior … then flag the conflict for human review"), the ticket itself remains the canonical record. **Reviewer decision needed**: do we want to add a short "How edit checks are flagged" paragraph to GUIDE-021 that summarizes the flagging logic per program type? That would mean reaching past the current scope of the guide.

Out of scope for guide narrative:
- NXT-56793 (resolved 2025-04-07, "Edit Check Report - Reverse Edit Check"): changes the *report page* (GUIDE-025 Edit Check Report section), not the Edit Checks operational page. See GUIDE-025 enumeration below.

