## GUIDE-025 (Accountability Reports) — full enumeration of all 48 candidate tickets

No edits were applied to GUIDE-025 in this pass. The guide is large and describes ~14 reports at a high level (Select X / Click GENERATE / DOWNLOAD). Most candidate tickets change column-level details or add multi-select dropdowns; applying them inline would inflate the guide well beyond its current scope and risk introducing the kind of over-reach the anti-hallucination rules guard against. The full list is below for SME triage.

Per-ticket disposition uses these dispositions:
- **Already documented** — the high-level concept is in the existing guide
- **No nav surface** — backend / behavior / processing change with no clickpath impact
- **Conditional feature** — gated on a system setting that not all districts have
- **Column-level UI** — small column or label change inside an existing report's output
- **Page-wide overhaul** — multi-select dropdowns and new date picker (common pattern across many reports)
- **New report / variant** — adds an entirely new report or report option
- **Out of scope** — affects a different page than GUIDE-025

