**Recommended SME next actions for GUIDE-025:**
1. Decide whether to add a single global note at the top of GUIDE-025 stating "Most report pages now support multi-select on Site, Site Type, Meal Type, and similar filters; the date picker on all report pages was upgraded to the FOH Dashboard date picker version." If yes, this single note would cite the page-wide-overhaul tickets (NXT-62612, NXT-62629, NXT-62700, NXT-62701, NXT-63974, NXT-63975, NXT-63978, NXT-63979, NXT-63977, NXT-63976). This avoids editing every report section individually.
2. Decide whether to add per-report column-level details (NXT-71620, NXT-71622, NXT-71623, NXT-70587, NXT-70002, NXT-70001, NXT-66923). The current guide intentionally describes reports at the page-flow level, not the column level; documenting each column change would be a scope shift.
3. Decide which conditional features (Attendance Feature reports, State Eligibility reports) belong in the guide vs. only in district-specific onboarding material.
4. For CACFP report variants (NXT-64498, NXT-64518, NXT-64519, NXT-64507), the existing guide is SNP-flavored; should a parallel CACFP section be added, or are CACFP-specific guides the right home?

