## Open questions / ambiguities for human review

1. **NXT-67405 (Edit Checks logic for CACFP/CEP)** — see GUIDE-021 Flagged section above. Behavior-only change to flag-triggering rules; the user's clickpath is unchanged. Per CLAUDE.md authority rule, this lives in the ticket/spec. Confirm or override.
2. **GUIDE-014 / NXT-53700 (Expected Deposit timestamp)** — the current guide does not describe the Expected Deposit display. Should the SME want this documented, the ticket specifies the format `Expected Deposit (As of {{CreatedDate}})` with a current-time line beneath it; flagged here so it does not get lost.
3. **GUIDE-018 (Transaction Adjustments)** — NXT-58250 (2025-07-28) restructures the Adjustments page (removes nested grids, adds custom views, new columns: Serving Site, Enrollment Site, User Name; new grid-column filters). The current guide was not loaded for this pass because the scope of restructure is large and the existing curated narrative may need a holistic rewrite rather than targeted inline edits. Defer to a follow-up curation pass.
4. **GUIDE-020 (Eligibility Variance)** — NXT-45480 (2024-03-15) adds State Eligibility formatting to Serving Exceptions when the state-eligibility system setting is on. Skipped in this pass because it is conditional on a setting and the existing guide does not mention eligibility formatting at all; needs an SME judgement on whether to document a conditional feature.
5. **GUIDE-015 (Transactions Search) / NXT-70014 and GUIDE-011 / NXT-70013** — the Square integration tickets ship with image-only descriptions in the CSV. Skipped to avoid inventing UI details from a thumbnail.
6. **GUIDE-012 (Unbalanced Session) / Bulk Adjustment (NXT-41518, NXT-41520, NXT-44531)** — Bulk Adjustment is a substantial new workflow on the Reconciliation page, but the current Unbalanced Session guide does not introduce the More Actions menu at all. Adding a Bulk Adjustment subsection here would mean introducing the More Actions context from scratch (similar to what was done for Delete Session in GUIDE-013). Left for SME review because the same workflow may be better placed in GUIDE-018 (Transaction Adjustments) where bulk operations naturally belong.
